<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>üìä Financial Criteria Checklist</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      margin: 40px;
      background-color: #f8f9fa;
    }
    h1 {
      color: #333;
    }
    .criteria {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      padding: 10px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
    }
    .highlighted {
      background-color: #d4edda;
    }
    label {
      cursor: pointer;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    .tooltip {
      border-bottom: 1px dotted #000;
      cursor: help;
      position: relative;
    }
    .tooltip:hover::after {
      content: attr(data-tooltip);
      position: absolute;
      background: #333;
      color: #fff;
      padding: 6px;
      border-radius: 5px;
      font-size: 0.85em;
      top: 25px;
      left: 0;
      white-space: nowrap;
      z-index: 1000;
    }
    #translateBtn {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      padding: 8px 16px;
      font-size: 1em;
      background-color: #007bff;
      color: white;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 6px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
    #progressTracker {
      margin-bottom: 30px;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>üìä Financial Criteria Checklist</h1>
  <button id="translateBtn" onclick="translatePage()">–†—É—Å—Å–∫–∏–π</button>
  <p id="progressTracker">0 of 6 criteria selected</p>

  <div class="criteria" id="group1">
    <input type="checkbox" id="criteria1" onchange="toggleHighlight('criteria1', 'group1'); updateProgress();">
    <label for="criteria1">Previous 5-Year Revenue Growth of 50%</label>
    <p id="text1">Think of a company like a football player or boxer‚Äîone that‚Äôs already successful is more likely to win in the future than one that‚Äôs not.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="criteria" id="group2">
    <input type="checkbox" id="criteria2" onchange="toggleHighlight('criteria2', 'group2'); updateProgress();">
    <label for="criteria2">Debt to Equity (DE) Ratio Less Than 1.5</label>
    <p id="text2">Statistically, companies with lower debt tend to deliver better future results.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="criteria" id="group3">
    <input type="checkbox" id="criteria3" onchange="toggleHighlight('criteria3', 'group3'); updateProgress();">
    <label for="criteria3"><span class="tooltip" data-tooltip="Price/Earnings to Growth (PEG) is a ratio used to determine a stock‚Äôs value while factoring in growth.">PEG</span> Ratio Under 1.5</label>
    <p id="text3">Suggests reasonable stock pricing relative to growth potential.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="criteria" id="group4">
    <input type="checkbox" id="criteria4" onchange="toggleHighlight('criteria4', 'group4'); updateProgress();">
    <label for="criteria4">Positive Cash Flow</label>
    <p id="text4">Consistent cash inflow gives a company a safety buffer during market downturns.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="criteria" id="group5">
    <input type="checkbox" id="criteria5" onchange="toggleHighlight('criteria5', 'group5'); updateProgress();">
    <label for="criteria5">Return on Equity (ROE) Above 20%</label>
    <p id="text5">Strong ROE means the company turns $1 of investor capital into $2 or more.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="criteria" id="group6">
    <input type="checkbox" id="criteria6" onchange="toggleHighlight('criteria6', 'group6'); updateProgress();">
    <label for="criteria6"><span class="tooltip" data-tooltip="Is there growing demand for this company‚Äôs product or service?">Future Market Demand</span></label>
    <p id="text6">Assess what customers, trends, and analysts say about future relevance.</p>
  </div>

<script>
  function toggleHighlight(checkboxId, groupId) {
    const checkbox = document.getElementById(checkboxId);
    const group = document.getElementById(groupId);
    group.classList.toggle("highlighted", checkbox.checked);
  }

  function updateProgress() {
    const total = 6;
    let checked = 0;
    for (let i = 1; i <= total; i++) {
      if (document.getElementById(`criteria${i}`).checked) {
        checked++;
      }
    }
    document.getElementById("progressTracker").textContent = `${checked} of ${total} criteria selected`;
  }

  document.querySelectorAll("input[type='checkbox']").forEach(cb => {
    cb.addEventListener("change", updateProgress);
  });

  updateProgress();

